    participant Controller as KServe Controller<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant StorageInit as Storage Initializer<br/>(Init Container)
    participant S3 as S3/GCS/Azure<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Client as External Client
    participant IstioGW as Istio Ingress Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KnativeGW as Knative Local Gateway<br/>80/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant ModelPod as Model Server Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,ModelPod: Flow 1: InferenceService Deployment (Serverless Mode)

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. Create InferenceService CR<br/>Bearer Token Auth
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Admission webhook call<br/>TLS, API Server cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated/Mutated response
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 3. Watch event received<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Create Knative Service,<br/>VirtualService, ExternalName Service

    Note over StorageInit,S3: Model Loading
    StorageInit->>S3: 5. Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+, Cloud credentials
    S3-->>StorageInit: Model artifacts

    Note over Client,ModelPod: Inference Request Flow
    Client->>IstioGW: 6. POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+, Optional OAuth
    IstioGW->>KnativeGW: 7. Route via VirtualService<br/>HTTP, Istio mTLS
    KnativeGW->>ModelPod: 8. Forward to model server<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP
    ModelPod-->>KnativeGW: Prediction response
    KnativeGW-->>IstioGW: Response
    IstioGW-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over User,ModelPod: Flow 2: RawDeployment with Gateway API

    participant OSHGW as OpenShift Gateway<br/>(openshift-ai-inference)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ModelSvc as Model Server Service<br/>80/TCP HTTP

    Client->>OSHGW: 5. HTTPS request<br/>TLS 1.2+
    OSHGW->>ModelSvc: 6. Route via HTTPRoute<br/>HTTP 80/TCP
    ModelSvc-->>OSHGW: Response
    OSHGW-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over User,ModelPod: Flow 3: LLMInferenceService with Scheduler

    participant GW as Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant EPP as llm-d Scheduler<br/>9002/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant LLMPod as LLM Model Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP

    Client->>GW: 1. HTTPS request via HTTPRoute<br/>TLS 1.2+
    GW->>EPP: 2. ext_proc call<br/>gRPC 9002/TCP, TLS self-signed, mTLS
    EPP->>LLMPod: 3. Scheduled request<br/>HTTP 8000/TCP
    LLMPod-->>EPP: Response
    EPP-->>GW: Routing decision
    GW-->>Client: Response
